messages.content: Tell me about this dandiset. *

This DANDI dataset (DANDI:001195, version 0.250408.1733) is titled:

**"Separable Dorsal Raphe Dopamine Projections Mediate the Facets of Loneliness-like State"**

### Overview

- **Focus:** It explores how distinct projections from dorsal raphe dopamine neurons mediate different behavioral and motivational facets associated with loneliness in mice.
- **Types of Data:** The dataset contains both in vivo calcium imaging data with supporting behavioral videos and ex vivo patch-clamp electrophysiology recordings.
- **Species:** Mus musculus (house mouse)
- **Data Format:** All data are stored in the Neurodata Without Borders (NWB) format.
- **Sample Size:** 
  - 34 subjects (mice)
  - 131 cells recorded
  - 8 samples
  - 230 files (~70 GB total)
- **Measurements Include:** 
  - Current clamp & voltage clamp electrophysiology
  - One-photon calcium imaging
  - Optical stimulation (optogenetics)
  - Video monitoring of behaviors

### Study Highlights

- Examines the distinct roles of dorsal raphe dopamine projections to the bed nucleus of the stria terminalis (BNST), central amygdala (CeA), and posterior basolateral amygdala (BLP).
- Investigates how these projections differentially affect social motivation, exploratory behavior, and aversive states in mice.
- Integrates calcium imaging and electrophysiological insights with behavioral outcomes.

### Keywords

- Optogenetics, behavior videos, calcium imaging, electrophysiology, social isolation, social motivation, mouse behavior, dorsal raphe nucleus, dopamine.

### Citation & Metadata

- **Citation:** Keyes, Laurel; Lee, Christopher R.; Wichmann, Romy; Matthews, Gillian A.; Tye, Kay M. (2025) Separable Dorsal Raphe Dopamine Projections Mediate the Facets of Loneliness-like State (Version 0.250408.1733) [Data set]. DANDI Archive. https://doi.org/10.48324/dandi.001195/0.250408.1733
- **License:** CC-BY-4.0 (Open Access)
- **DOI:** 10.48324/dandi.001195/0.250408.1733
- **Link:** [DANDI:001195 on DANDI Archive](https://dandiarchive.org/dandiset/001195/0.250408.1733)

### Notes

The dataset is relevant to systems neuroscience, behavioral analysis, and studies of social motivation and loneliness using advanced neurophysiological and imaging techniques.
